headline: Starbucks Lawsuit And Supply Strains Test Turnaround And Brand Resilience
summary: Former Starbucks executive files wrongful termination and sex discrimination lawsuit linked to Siren System health and safety concerns. Lawsuit claims management pushed to understate equipment malfunctions, food safety incidents, and profitability risks. Starbucks, NasdaqGS:SBUX, is also working through supply chain issues affecting items such as milk and pastries. These issues emerge during the new CEO's turnaround plan, a key period for the brand's store operations and reputation. For you...
